{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-publisher-theme","result":{"pageContext":{"id":2044,"date":"2022-12-06T14:28:15","date_gmt":"2022-12-06T14:28:15","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=2044"},"modified":"2022-12-06T21:42:15","modified_gmt":"2022-12-06T21:42:15","slug":"how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-publisher-theme","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-publisher-theme/","title":{"rendered":"How to fix broken zoom on &#8220;Publisher&#8221; theme"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Publish theme is one of the more recent free themes made available by the Shopify developers, boasting an innovative design that is both informative and easy on the eyes, offering sellers an opportunity to provide their clients with a smooth, straight to the point experience.<br><br>One downside it shares with many free themes however is that its default zoom functionality has some issues, the most egregious one being mobile devices displaying super sized images that are hard and cumbersome to scroll. But that can be easily solved by our <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/dawn-theme-zoom-slider-pro\">Zoom Slider</a>!<br><br>You might be confused as to how code meant for the Dawn theme could fix your issues with the Publisher theme, but an interesting thing to know about Shopify is that most free themes have very similar code and our Zoom Slider was written to be as versatile as possible. It can be installed in you Publisher theme store by following a very simple process and it&#8217;ll be a perfect match!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-making-a-backup-of-your-theme\">Making a backup of your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-downloading-the-code-files\">Downloading the code files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can acquire the code needed for this tutorial <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/dawn-theme-zoom-slider-pro\">here</a> as well as see it working in our <a href=\"https://pandashopdeals.myshopify.com/products/ezfy-dawn-zoom-slider\">live preview</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-step-by-step\">Step by step</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Go to your store&#8217;s admin and navigate <strong>Online Store &gt; Themes &gt; Actions &gt; Edit Code</strong> to reach the store&#8217;s code editor.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1216\" height=\"328\" class=\"wp-image-2050\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_2.png\" alt=\"Opening the Impulse theme code editor from the Shopify admin\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_2.png 1216w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_2-850x229.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_2-1200x324.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_2-768x207.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1216px) 100vw, 1216px\" /><br></li><li>At the menu in the left open the <strong>Snippets </strong>folder and click <strong>Add a new snippet</strong>. In the window that appears name the new snippet the following:<br><br><code>ezfy-zoom</code><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1401\" height=\"698\" class=\"wp-image-2046\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom1.png\" alt=\"Naming the &quot;ezfy-zoom&quot; snippet\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom1.png 1401w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom1-850x423.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom1-1200x598.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom1-768x383.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1401px) 100vw, 1401px\" /><br></li><li>Open the folder you downloaded and inside you&#8217;ll find a file called <strong>ezfy-zoom.txt</strong>. Open it and copy everything in it.<br></li><li>Paste the code you just copied into the file you just created and click the &#8220;save&#8221; button on the top right corner of the code editor.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"430\" class=\"wp-image-2048\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430-1.jpg\" alt=\"Saving the &quot;ezfy-zoom&quot; file\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430-1.jpg 1536w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430-1-850x238.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430-1-1200x336.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430-1-768x215.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" /><br></li><li>Now open the <strong>Sections</strong> folder on the left side menu and find the <strong>theme.liquid</strong> file. Open it.<br></li><li>Press <strong>CTRL + F</strong> (or <strong>CMD + F </strong>on <strong>Mac</strong>)&nbsp;to open the search bar, use it to find the following code:<br><br><code>&lt;/body&gt;</code><br><br>Then paste in the following right <strong>above </strong>the <strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong> line:<br><br><code>{% include 'ezfy-zoom' %} </code><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"698\" class=\"wp-image-2052\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ezfy-zoom-3.jpg\" alt=\"Adding the ezfy-zoom snippet to the theme.liquid file\"><br><br>Now you just need to save it again and you&#8217;re done!<br></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-conclusion\">Conclusion<br></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The zoom functionality for your Publisher store has now been greatly improved! Look at the examples below, the default zoom shows the product image at full resolution even in smaller mobile devices. Users are forced to scroll all the way across huge pictures while incapable of seeing it at an appropriate size.<br><br> <img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"400\" height=\"370\" class=\"wp-image-2055\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_3.png\" alt=\"Publisher theme default zoom\"><br><br>Now with your new Ezfy zoom slider, you can see the whole picture at a zoom level appropriate to your current device:<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"400\" height=\"398\" class=\"wp-image-2057\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_4.png\" alt=\"Zoom slider working in the Publisher theme\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_4.png 400w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Screenshot_4-200x200.png 200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" /><br><br>And to top it off, your pictures now also have arrow icons that allow your clients&#8217; to easily jump over from image to image, providing a much improved experience while browsing your store! And if there&#8217;s any further features you&#8217;d like to implement, just send us an email at <strong>ezfycode@gmail.com</strong> and we&#8217;ll be ready to talk to you for a free quote.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-you-may-also-like\">You may also like</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/add-slideshow-shopify-no-apps\">&#8211; How